I've put a lot of work into getting Love to build with emscripten using the existing Love cmake build system. Everything seems to be working now. It's still not for the faint of heart but everything is much more consolidated and straightforward than it was before.<br /><br />It requires, of course, the emscripten SDK to be installed. This project won't compile with the released binaries so you will need to use the pseudo-release tagged as `sdk-incoming-64bit`. If you can get that compiled and installed then the rest of this should be a cakewalk.<br /><br />Clone my fork of Megasource.<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://bitbucket.org/TannerRogalsky/megasource">https://bitbucket.org/TannerRogalsky/megasource</a><!-- m --><br /><br />And then clone my fork of Love into `libs/love` as per the megasource instructions.<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://bitbucket.org/TannerRogalsky/love">https://bitbucket.org/TannerRogalsky/love</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Check out the `emscripten` branch of each of these. Then make a build folder inside of megasource and run `emcmake cmake -H.. -B. &amp;&amp; emmake make`. It should spit out a debug `.js` build.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://love2d.org/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=45757">Tanner</a> — Thu Mar 17, 2016 7:26 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
